DTSTAMP:20260422T055011Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a guided walkthrough of the Living Botanicals installation in the MAP’s Sculpture courtyard led by its grower Kush Sethi. Kush is a gardener and a forager from Delhi who has helped us create a living and breathing space\, in collaboration with Architect Bhavana La Noche. In May\, he returns to engage our audiences with gardening and walkthroughs of the plants in this installation.\n\nCome along to hear tales behind this garden’s inception\, behind-the-scenes and stories of plants from Hortus Malabaricus to Bangalore. Spend time in this living ecosystem observing plants from the lens of an explorer. We have also provided a field kit of assorted lenses which will allow you to zoom into the ecology of this garden. Bring a diary to draw\, press things and take notes.
DTEND:20260509T061500Z
DTSTART:20260509T053000Z
SUMMARY:Living Botanicals
UID:1258@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/living-botanicals-3/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-16T135104.422.png
CATEGORIES:Performances,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260421T062917Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a rehearsed reading of an excerpt from Malegalalli Madhumagalu by Kuvempu and revisit the landscape of Malenadu through stories of land\, labour\, and everyday life. Framed through the lens of colonial intervention in the Western Ghats\, the session reflects on how ecologies and communities were reshaped in its wake.\n\nThis is an invitation to listen closely to language\, memory\, and the histories they carry.\n\nThis event is in Kannada.\n\nThis programme is in conjunction with MAP’s ongoing exhibition Paper Gardens: Art\, Botany and Empire.
DTEND:20260426T130000Z
DTSTART:20260426T113000Z
SUMMARY:Rehearsed Reading - Kuvempu's 'Malegalalli Madumagalu'
UID:1255@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/rehearsed-reading-kuvempus-malegalalli-madumagalu/
END:VEVENT
